Reasoning: The paper discusses various approaches to the notion of information, including Shannon entropy and Kolmogorov complexity, which are commonly studied in the field of information theory (cs.IT). The two main applications of Kolmogorov complexity discussed in the paper are randomness and classification, which are topics of interest in machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also touches on the duality between information and computation, which is a topic of interest in theoretical computer science (cs.CC) and cryptography (cs.CR).
